Most babies born with diaphragmatic defects have very small lungs , and many die in the newborn period with severe breathing difficulties .
It is unknown whether the small lungs occur because these children have a diaphragmatic defect , or whether some patients might have a <termsem="SO:0000704"> genetic </term> abnormality that affects the development of both the lung and the diaphragm simultaneously .
