We screened mice treated with the chemical mutagen N-ethyl-N-nitrosourea ( ENU ) for lines with developmental defects that present in the perinatal period [ 14 ] .
From this screen , we identified a line of mice carrying a recessive <termsem="SO:0001059"> mutation </term> that results in primary pulmonary hypoplasia and abnormal diaphragmatic and cardiac development .
<termsem="SO:0000001"> Positional </term> cloning analysis identified Fog2 ( Zfpm2 ) as a likely candidate , and <termsem="SO:0000352"> DNA </term> sequencing revealed a <termsem="SO:0001059"> mutation </term> in a <termsem="SO:0000163"> splice donor site </term> that generates an abnormal <termsem="SO:0000673"> transcript </term> encoding a truncated protein .
