There were incomplete lung fissures bilaterally .
A deep posterior diaphragmatic eventration was present on the left side .
Additionally , two muscularized ligamentous bands resembling diaphragmatic remnants encircled the left lobe of the liver , creating an abnormal fissured liver contour .
Away from the eventration , the diaphragm appeared well muscularized , measuring 0.3 cm in thickness .
A complete autopsy revealed no other malformations ; the heart was determined to be grossly normal and was donated for valve harvest .
